---
// Honest pre-beta terms draft. Plain-English, no warranty, describes
// the service as it actually behaves today. Final lawyer-reviewed copy
// is tracked in docs/blocked-by-human.md.
import Legal from "../layouts/Legal.astro";
---

<Legal
  title="Terms — nlqdb"
  description="Plain-English pre-beta terms for nlqdb: the service is provided as-is while we build, anonymous databases are temporary, use it lawfully."
  heading="Terms of use"
  canonical="/terms"
  updated="13 June 2026"
>
  <p>
    These are plain-English terms for using nlqdb while it's in pre-beta. By
    using the site or the service, you agree to them.
  </p>

  <h2>Pre-beta, as-is</h2>
  <p>
    nlqdb is early software under active development. It's provided
    <strong>as-is, with no warranty</strong>. Features can change, break, or
    disappear without notice, and we can't promise it will always be available
    or error-free. Don't rely on it for anything critical yet.
  </p>

  <h2>Your data and databases</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Databases you create anonymously are <strong>temporary</strong> and may
      be deleted automatically (anonymous databases currently expire about 72
      hours after creation). Sign in to keep one.
    </li>
    <li>
      You're responsible for the content you put into nlqdb and for having the
      right to use it.
    </li>
    <li>
      We may delete data or accounts to keep the service running, prevent
      abuse, or stay within our free-tier limits during pre-beta.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
  <p>Please don't:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Use nlqdb to break the law or infringe anyone's rights.</li>
    <li>
      Attempt to overload, probe, or abuse the service, or work around usage
      limits and bot protections.
    </li>
    <li>Upload data you're not allowed to share.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Liability</h2>
  <p>
    To the extent the law allows, nlqdb isn't liable for any loss arising from
    using a pre-beta service. Use it at your own risk.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes</h2>
  <p>
    These terms will be replaced with a formal, lawyer-reviewed version before
    general availability. Questions:
    <a href="mailto:hello@nlqdb.com">hello@nlqdb.com</a>.
  </p>
</Legal>

<style>
  /* /terms is intentionally unobtrusive (redesign-plan §5). See the
   * matching block in privacy.astro for the rationale — the two pages
   * share the Legal layout and apply identical scoped overrides so the
   * lime accents, mono headers, and decorative borders from the legacy
   * layout collapse into the quiet-brutalism token system. */
  :global(.legal__kicker) {
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  :global(.legal__title) {
    font-family: var(--display);
    font-size: var(--t-section);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  :global(.legal__updated) {
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  :global(.legal__note) {
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    background: transparent;
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: var(--t-body);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  :global(.legal__body h2) {
    font-family: var(--display);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: var(--t-large);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    line-height: 1.2;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: clamp(32px, 5vw, 44px) 0 12px;
  }

  :global(.legal__body p),
  :global(.legal__body li) {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: var(--t-body);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--body);
  }

  :global(.legal__body a) {
    color: var(--ink);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-thickness: 1px;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }

  :global(.legal__body a:hover) {
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  :global(.legal__body strong) {
    color: var(--ink);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  :global(.legal__cta) {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }

  :global(.legal__cta .btn--accent) {
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--ink);
    border-color: var(--rule);
    box-shadow: none;
  }

  :global(.legal__cta .btn--accent:hover) {
    color: var(--ink);
    border-color: var(--ink);
    transform: none;
    box-shadow: none;
  }
</style>
